Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep roundup: Tarolly sisters advance to state TIMES STAFF REPORT 9:53 p.m. CDT October 17, 2015 Sports brief (Photo: Times graphic) 
SARTELL — Sisters Ashley, Taylor and Katelyn Tarolly are all heading to the Class 2A individual state tournament for the St. Cloud Tech girls tennis team. 
The three placed first in singles and doubles competition at the Section 8-2A playoffs Saturday at Fitness Evolution. 
Ashley, a seventh-grader, won 6-3, 6-1 in singles competition to win the Section 8-2A title. 
Katelyn, a sophomore, and Taylor, a junior, won 6-2, 6-2 in doubles competition to clinch a spot at state. 
Rocori’s Brynn Sauer, a sophomore, took second in singles play and advanced to state. Bemidji’s Abbie Kelm and Alexis Konecne took second in doubles play to advance to state. 
The Class 2A individual state tournament will begin Oct. 29 at the Baseline Tennis Center in Minneapolis. 
VOLLEYBALL 
ROCHESTER INVITATIONAL 
ROCHESTER — Sauk Rapids finished in sixth place at the Rochester Invitational. 
The Storm won their first match against Rochester Lourdes 2-1 (25-16, 20-25, 15-3), before falling to Forest Lake 2-1 (20-25, 25-15, 15-8) in the fifth-place match. 
Kyra Harvey had 18 digs and 17 kills, Kahlen Manthey had 29 digs and three ace serves and Morgan Held had 28 set assists on the day to lead Sauk Rapids (15-9 overall).
